[Student "S"]
{After SOUTH's 2\C opening, NORTH bids 2NT, showing a balanced hand of at least 8 points. NORTH 
actually has 12 points, but the time to show the extra strength will be later.

SOUTH's 3\C bid is Stayman, asking NORTH for a 4-card Major. NORTH mentions his \Ss and 
SOUTH bids 4\S, showing a minimum 2\C opener with 4 \Ss.

Now NORTH adds his 12 points to SOUTH's 22 minimum and gets 34. He bids 6\S.}

