[Student "S"]
{WEST has 3 points, so she responds 2\D to EAST's opening 2\C bid, 
then bids 3\C as a second-negative when EAST bids 2\S.

However, when EAST then bids \Hs, WEST finds two more points 
and bids 4\H.}

